"{\"uid\": \"rte.ie-news-ireland-2024-0726-1461951-paris-green-olympics\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"With medals made of iron salvaged from Eiffel Tower refurbishments and stadium seating of recycled plastic, Paris 2024 aims to be the greenest Olympics yet.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 156, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The case for action is clear as scientists have said intense heat linked to man-made carbon emissions is a growing risk to competitors at the world's largest sporting event and beyond.\", \"from\": 158, \"to\": 342, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Paris 2024 has pledged to reduce its carbon emissions by half compared to the average emitted during the London and Rio Summer Games.\", \"from\": 344, \"to\": 477, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 344, \"end\": 354, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2024_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.5204909683914832e-21, \"text\": \"Paris 2024\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2024_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2024_Summer_Olympics\"}, {\"begin\": 449, \"end\": 455, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/London\", \"score\": 0.9217526343951375, \"rank\": 0.08486239518030912, \"text\": \"London\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/London\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/London\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Here are some of Paris 2024's efforts towards meeting that goal.\", \"from\": 479, \"to\": 543, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 496, \"end\": 506, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2024_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.5204909683914832e-21, \"text\": \"Paris 2024\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2024_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2024_Summer_Olympics\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Construction  For many people, Olympic stadiums such as Rio's Olympic Aquatic Centre that have failed to find a purpose after the Games symbolise extravagance.\", \"from\": 545, \"to\": 704, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 601, \"end\": 604, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Earth_Summit\", \"score\": 0.9999943475523331, \"rank\": 5.004388160879662e-06, \"text\": \"Rio\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Earth_Summit\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Earth_Summit\"}, {\"begin\": 607, \"end\": 629, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Athens_Olympic_Sports_Complex\", \"score\": 0.9999990330498022, \"rank\": 9.669509147702626e-07, \"text\": \"Olympic Aquatic Centre\", \"types\": [\"Q41176\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Athens_Olympic_Sports_Complex\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Athens_Olympic_Sports_Complex\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Paris 2024 has sought to minimise new construction.\", \"from\": 706, \"to\": 757, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 706, \"end\": 716, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2024_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.5204909683914832e-21, \"text\": \"Paris 2024\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2024_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2024_Summer_Olympics\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Almost all venues use existing or temporary sites, often relying on the city's landmarks as backdrops.\", \"from\": 759, \"to\": 861, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Organisers say the replacement of concrete with low carbon building materials, including sustainably-sourced wood, will reduce the Olympic Village's emissions by 30% compared to what the organisers referred to as conventional projects without giving details.\", \"from\": 863, \"to\": 1121, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 994, \"end\": 1009, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympic_Village\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.285773115590006e-15, \"text\": \"Olympic Village\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympic_Village\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympic_Village\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Permanent infrastructure accounted for 73% of the estimated 467,000 tonnes of carbon emissions generated by the Olympic Games between 2018 and 2023.\", \"from\": 1123, \"to\": 1271, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"In addition, 11,000 seats at the only two purpose-built arenas for Paris 2024 are made out of recycled plastic.\", \"from\": 1273, \"to\": 1384, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1340, \"end\": 1350, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2024_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.5204909683914832e-21, \"text\": \"Paris 2024\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2024_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2024_Summer_Olympics\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Transport  Along with construction, transport is expected to be one of the biggest sources of emissions during the event.\", \"from\": 1386, \"to\": 1507, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Organisers have said they will use low-carbon vehicles to ferry around athletes and official visitors and that all venues are accessible by bike, foot or public transport.\", \"from\": 1509, \"to\": 1680, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"However, Paris is not tackling the emissions generated by spectators travelling to the Games.\", \"from\": 1682, \"to\": 1775, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1691, \"end\": 1696, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.1186626405116135e-13, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Such emissions made up almost a third (28%) of the 3.3 million tonnes of carbon emitted by the London 2012 Games.\", \"from\": 1777, \"to\": 1890, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1872, \"end\": 1889, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2012_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"London 2012 Games\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2012_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2012_Summer_Olympics\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Renewable Power  Paris 2024 has said its venues will use renewable energy sources via the grid, rather than the diesel-powered generators often used at sporting venues.\", \"from\": 1892, \"to\": 2060, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Some 5,000sq/m of solar panels have been installed on the roof of the Aquatics Centre and Olympic Village, and a 400sq/m floating solar farm set up on the River Seine.\", \"from\": 2062, \"to\": 2229, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2152, \"end\": 2167, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympic_Village\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.285773115590006e-15, \"text\": \"Olympic Village\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympic_Village\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympic_Village\"}, {\"begin\": 2217, \"end\": 2228, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"River Seine\", \"types\": [\"Q47521\", \"Q4022\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Meanwhile, the Olympic Village has a cooling system that draws water from underground rather than air conditioning.\", \"from\": 2231, \"to\": 2346, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2246, \"end\": 2261, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympic_Village\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.285773115590006e-15, \"text\": \"Olympic Village\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympic_Village\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympic_Village\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"State-owned utility EDF told Reuters it would provide guarantees of origin to link the energy used by the Games to six wind and two solar production sites in France.\", \"from\": 2348, \"to\": 2513, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2377, \"end\": 2384, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Reuters\", \"score\": 0.9999999980550456, \"rank\": 1.898111596425649e-09, \"text\": \"Reuters\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Reuters\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Reuters\"}, {\"begin\": 2506, \"end\": 2512, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.9998656884638484, \"rank\": 0.00011574224356741105, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Carbon offsets  To make up for the some of the emissions that are not being avoided, notably spectator air travel, Paris 2024 has purchased 1.3 million carbon credits.\", \"from\": 2515, \"to\": 2682, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Each credit represents one tonne of emissions reduced or removed elsewhere - from projects protecting biodiversity-rich forests in Kenya and Guatemala and improving access to clean cooking in Kenya, Nigeria and the Democratic Republic of Congo.\", \"from\": 2684, \"to\": 2928, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2815, \"end\": 2820, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kenya\", \"score\": 0.9999999999772626, \"rank\": 1.8659738756454797e-11, \"text\": \"Kenya\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kenya\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kenya\"}, {\"begin\": 2825, \"end\": 2834, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Guatemala\", \"score\": 0.9999738371082574, \"rank\": 2.4379230450931644e-05, \"text\": \"Guatemala\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Guatemala\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Guatemala\"}, {\"begin\": 2876, \"end\": 2881, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kenya\", \"score\": 0.9999999999772626, \"rank\": 1.8659738756454797e-11, \"text\": \"Kenya\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kenya\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kenya\"}, {\"begin\": 2883, \"end\": 2890, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nigeria\", \"score\": 0.9999999578321885, \"rank\": 4.216787813459824e-08, \"text\": \"Nigeria\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nigeria\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nigeria\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Organisers are also spending \\u20ac600,000 on four forestry projects in France to sequester 14,500 tonnes of greenhouse gases.\", \"from\": 2930, \"to\": 3051, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2997, \"end\": 3003, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.9998656884638484, \"rank\": 0.00011574224356741105, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Although carbon credits can channel money to climate-friendly projects, often in the global south, some credit-generating projects have been scrutinised over false claims about the benefits they deliver.\", \"from\": 3053, \"to\": 3256, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Paris 2024 had positioned itself as the first climate-positive Games in reference to plans to remove, reduce or offset more emissions than it generates.\", \"from\": 3258, \"to\": 3410, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"It has since dropped such claims, pledging instead to reduce its climate impact and support climate projects.\", \"from\": 3412, \"to\": 3521, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Source:Reuters    \\u00a9 RT\\u00c9 2026.\", \"from\": 3523, \"to\": 3552, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"RT\\u00c9.ie is the website of Raidi\\u00f3 Teilif\\u00eds \\u00c9ireann, Ireland's National Public Service Media.\", \"from\": 3553, \"to\": 3643, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3578, \"end\": 3601, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Raidi\\u00f3_Teilif\\u00eds_\\u00c9ireann\", \"score\": 0.9993664851270567, \"rank\": 0.0006339164685885233, \"text\": \"Raidi\\u00f3 Teilif\\u00eds \\u00c9ireann\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Raidi\\u00f3_Teilif\\u00eds_\\u00c9ireann\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Raidi\\u00f3_Teilif\\u00eds_\\u00c9ireann\"}, {\"begin\": 3603, \"end\": 3610, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Republic_of_Ireland\", \"score\": 0.9999999999936335, \"rank\": 6.375984514734633e-12, \"text\": \"Ireland\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Republic_of_Ireland\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Republic_of_Ireland\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"RT\\u00c9 is not responsible for the content of external internet sites.\", \"from\": 3644, \"to\": 3710, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3644, \"end\": 3647, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Raidi\\u00f3_Teilif\\u00eds_\\u00c9ireann\", \"score\": 0.9835396432123026, \"rank\": 0.013767790549921992, \"text\": \"RT\\u00c9\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Raidi\\u00f3_Teilif\\u00eds_\\u00c9ireann\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Raidi\\u00f3_Teilif\\u00eds_\\u00c9ireann\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Images Courtesy of Getty Images.\", \"from\": 3712, \"to\": 3744, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3731, \"end\": 3736, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Getty_Images\", \"score\": 0.9999665584303574, \"rank\": 2.7995418764761703e-05, \"text\": \"Getty\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Getty_Images\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Getty_Images\"}]}]}"